 He thanked the waitress with a charming smile, not paying attention to the cup of coffee that was placed infront of him, but to her. She held his gaze aswell, and couldn't contain a bashful smirk herself before whisking off back to the main counter.
 "You just can't help yourself can you." Konstantin said, raising a forkful of noodles to his companion. "You're going to get yourself in trouble one of these days!"
 "I accept all the consequences of my actions." Replied Leo, "Be them bad, good... or very good." Leo took a wry sip of coffee as he finished his sentence, winking at Konstantin. "I am only here for a few days, and hey, what the girlfriend doesn't know can't hurt her."
